    <body>
      <trans-unit id="1" ns:sid="2047271449595539457" ns:tid="2047271801003651074" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="74">
        <source>Why Is the Battery Not Charged by PV Power?</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="2" ns:sid="2047271449595539458" ns:tid="2047271801003651075" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source>Battery SOC policy restrictions</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="3" ns:sid="2047271449595539459" ns:tid="2047271801003651076" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="44">
        <source>When the battery SOC reaches the preset <ph id="f0">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol158578277463&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207635068088.xml#144641&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298267098#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207635068088&quot;/&gt;</ph> (for example, 90%), the system will suspend charging to prevent the risk of overcharging.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="4" ns:sid="2047271449595539460" ns:tid="2047271801003651077" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source>System operating mode conflict</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="5" ns:sid="2047271449595539461" ns:tid="2047271801003651078" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="Inschakelen:" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="96">
        <source><ph id="f0">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol350524810366&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207663920538.xml#568815&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002332266381#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207663920538&quot;/&gt;</ph> enabled:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match">Inschakelen:</target>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="6" ns:sid="2047271449595539462" ns:tid="2047271801003651079" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="39">
        <source>If the <ph id="f0">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol115281716349&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207663920538.xml#568815&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002332266381#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207663920538&quot;/&gt;</ph> function is enabled, the system may prioritize selling surplus PV power rather than storing it in the battery.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="7" ns:sid="2047271449595539463" ns:tid="2047271801003651080" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b68981751569&quot;&gt;</bpt><ph id="f1">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol784414883513&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207635068172.xml#456541&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298267098#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207635068172&quot;/&gt;</ph> mode<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="8" ns:sid="2047271449595539464" ns:tid="2047271801003651081" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="49">
        <source>In <ph id="f0">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol55241626133415&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207635068172.xml#456541&quot; idp:usecustomid=&quot;x-wc://file=ZH-CN_TOPIC_0000207635068172.xml#456541&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298267098#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207635068172&quot;/&gt;</ph> mode, the system prioritizes using PV power to meet load requirements, and directly sells surplus power rather than storing it in the battery.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="9" ns:sid="2047271449595539465" ns:tid="2047271801003651082" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b489845195619&quot;&gt;</bpt>Incorrect <ph id="f1">&lt;uicontrol class=&quot;+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol &quot; id=&quot;uicontrol1891019245456&quot; conref=&quot;en-us_topic_0000207784470567.xml#438333&quot; idp:conrefpath=&quot;200650494000#EN-US_BOOKMAP_0000002298266790#EN-US_TOPIC_0000207784470567&quot;/&gt;</ph> mode configuration<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10" ns:sid="2047271449595539466" ns:tid="2047271801003651083" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="49">
        <source>If the PV power generation period is not manually set as the charging window, or the charging window does not cover the off-peak electricity price period, the system may not trigger battery charging.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="11" ns:sid="2047271449595539467" ns:tid="2047271801003651084" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="49">
        <source>Economic optimization policy</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="12" ns:sid="2047271449595539468" ns:tid="2047271801003651085" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="32">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b1945284711573&quot;&gt;</bpt>Insufficient peak-valley price difference<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="13" ns:sid="2047271449595539469" ns:tid="2047271801003651086" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="34">
        <source>If the difference between the feed-in electricity price (peak hours) and the electricity purchase price (off-peak hours) is small, the system may determine that selling electricity directly is more economical than the charge-discharge cycle.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="14" ns:sid="2047271449595539470" ns:tid="2047271801003651087" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="40">
        <source>Consequently, the system prioritizes feeding PV power to the grid rather than storing it.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="15" ns:sid="2047271449595539471" ns:tid="2047271801003651088" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="65">
        <source><bpt id="g0">&lt;b class=&quot;+ topic/ph hi-d/b &quot; id=&quot;b245384713576&quot;&gt;</bpt>Negative electricity price scenario<ept id="g0">&lt;/g&gt;</ept>:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="16" ns:sid="2047271449595539472" ns:tid="2047271801003651089" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="54">
        <source>When the electricity purchase price is negative, the system may prioritize purchasing electricity from the grid to charge the battery rather than use PV power.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="17" ns:sid="2047271449595539473" ns:tid="2047271801003651090" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="49">
        <source>Energy prediction and scheduling priority:</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="18" ns:sid="2047271449595539474" ns:tid="2047271801003651091" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="36">
        <source>The system uses historical data to forecast future electricity demand and price fluctuations.</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="19" ns:sid="2047271449595539475" ns:tid="2047271801003651092" translate="yes" ns:wfId="2047222835224051714" ns:wfName="T" ns:originTarget="" ns:Status="New" ns:Origin="" ns:MatchRate="31">
        <source>If the system forecasts that electricity prices will be lower or PV power will be more abundant in the future, it may temporarily suspend charging to wait for a better opportunity (for example, waiting until the electricity price is lower).</source>
        <target state="new" state-qualifier="fuzzy-match"/>
      </trans-unit>
    </body>
